links.clue: The lead guitarist of this band used to come up with strang phrases that eventually ended up as song titles. For instance, who ever thought there could be eight days in a week?
links.songInfoText: George Harrison used to come up with phrases like Hard Days Night and Eight Days a Week. John and Paul would just use them as song titles.

links.clue: George Harrison was sued for infringing the copyright of a song by this Band
links.hint1: The Band was named after a type of fabric
links.songInfoText: George Harrisons song My Sweet Lord was found by a court to have subconsciously plagiarised the song Hes So Fine by The Chiffons
